comment: Randle (LAL) makes incidental contact with Walker (CHA) that does not affect his SQBR.
Walker (CHA) makes incidental contact with Russell (LAL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Kaminsky (CHA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Russell (LAL) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Clarkson (LAL) makes incidental contact with Williams (CHA) during rebounding.
[Observable in enhanced video] Walker (CHA) moves his pivot foot.
Young (LAL) makes marginal contact with Walker (CHA) on the drive.
Batum (CHA) cleanly blocks the shot attempt by Clarkson (LAL).
Kaminsky (CHA) sets the screen on Clarkson (LAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Randle (LAL) legally contests Walker's (CHA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Clarkson (LAL) and Young (LAL) maintain legal guarding position on Walker (CHA).
Ingram (LAL) commits a take foul on Kaminsky (CHA).
Young (LAL) commits a take foul on Walker (CHA).
Clarkson (LAL) commits a take foul on Walker (CHA).
Randle (LAL) sets the screen on Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) and firms up his position upon contact. The two players briefly engage and separate following the screen.
